            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratori</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Caes</abbr><ex>ari</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Tit</abbr><ex>o</ex></expan></supplied> Aelio <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Hadr</abbr><ex>iano</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Ant</abbr><ex>onino</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan> Pio p</supplied><expan><abbr>on</abbr><ex>tifici</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imo</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> IIII <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>atri</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>atriae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>umerus</ex></expan> B</supplied><expan><abbr>r</abbr><ex>ittonum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>El</abbr><ex>antiensium</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Vor der Porta Praetoria gefunden und wohl ehemals über ihr angebracht. Fünf aneinanderpassende Fragmente und ein weiteres nicht anpassendes mit einer Darstellung des Mars erhalten. Inschriftfelde in Form einer tabula ansata; Figur des Mars in der rechten ansa. Zum Text vgl. CIL XIII 6490. Fundjahre: 1897 und 1929.</p>
            </div>
